<title>
Inspection of HVAC Control Unit and Its Circuit
</title>
<ptxt>
HVAC control unit and its circuits can be checked at HVAC control unit wiring connectors by measuring voltage.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
HVAC control unit can be checked only through connectors. It is strictly prohibited to connect voltmeter to HVAC control unit with connectors disconnected from it.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A7214015001">
<title>
Voltage Check
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove HVAC control unit. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A7216021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect G154 connector and G155 connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check voltage at each terminal.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
As each terminal voltage is affected by the battery voltage, confirm that battery voltage is 11 V or more with ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
